                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.812/61.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Minister of Nicaragua</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 21, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Secretary of State of the United States of America presents his compliments
                    to the Minister of Nicaragua and has the honor to acknowledge the receipt of the
                    memorandum of February 12 presented to the Department of State by the Minister
                    in regard to the proposed canal treaty between the United States and Nicaragua,
                    and to say that the substance of the memorandum has been communicated to the
                    President.</p>
            </div>
